<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Miss Necro - TZ</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-05 22:56:56</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>First i want to say that this is the first time I've played a Necromancer and that I haven't experimented with using the Vampiric Touch/Lifespike combo with tanking.  I do know that on a purely mana effiency basis this spell is GREAT.  <BR>
<BR>
From level 4-14 a cleric (the gods of healing) have to use Light Healing.  25 mana for up to 33 HPs.  This spell Heals 50 HPs for the same amount of mana!!!<BR>
<BR>
That's 50 HPs more for my pet, who is hitting YKs for up to 14 and bashing for up to 6...  it also looked like it healed around 25% of my pet's HPs. level 9 pet<BR>
<BR>
Darkness and Fear are often resisted and cost alot of mana, I can heal my pet for 100 HPs, like 50% or so of it's life and then sit and med while it battles on for the same mana it would cost to darkness and fear.<BR>
<BR>
Now I'm a poor little necro, I'm still using my newbie dagger and wearing cloth, so tanking gives me the willies.  Also, Lifespike does cost 18 mana and only gives me 11 HPs.  Granted those are HPs removed from my foe..<BR>
<BR>
I guess I have to save up to buy Vampiric Touch and some silk and try that combo out with tanking.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
